---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout 
  title="Does Your Business Really Need a Website in 2026? | Shelby Web Company"
  description="Explore why a website is still essential for businesses in 2026, despite the rise of social media and AI search."
>
  <article class="pt-32 pb-24 px-4 bg-[#0A0A0A]">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <!-- Header -->
      <header class="mb-16 text-center">
        <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-3 mb-6 px-4 py-1.5 rounded-full border border-brand-accent/20 bg-brand-accent/5">
          <span class="text-brand-accent text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest">Digital Strategy</span>
          <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-brand-accent/30"></span>
          <span class="text-brand-sky/60 text-xs font-medium uppercase tracking-widest">Vol #1 Article #2 • January 2026</span>
        </div>
        <h1 class="font-heading text-5xl md:text-7xl font-black text-white mb-8 tracking-tight leading-[1.1]">
          Does Your Business Really <br />
          <span class="text-transparent bg-clip-text bg-gradient-to-r from-brand-cyan to-brand-blue">Need a Website in 2026?</span>
        </h1>
        <p class="text-xl md:text-2xl text-brand-sky/80 leading-relaxed max-w-3xl mx-auto italic">
          And What Happens If You Don't
        </p>
      </header>

      <!-- Main Image Placeholder -->
      <div class="aspect-video bg-brand-dark border border-white/5 rounded-3xl mb-16 overflow-hidden shadow-2xl relative group">
        <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-br from-brand-blue/20 to-transparent opacity-50 group-hover:opacity-70 transition-opacity"></div>
        <div class="absolute inset-0 flex items-center justify-center text-center">
           <span class="text-brand-sky/20 font-heading text-4xl font-bold uppercase tracking-[0.2em] transform -rotate-12 px-4">The Future of <br/> Web Presence</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Content -->
      <div class="prose prose-invert prose-lg max-w-none">
        <p class="text-lg text-brand-sky/90 mb-12">
          For many years, "You need a website" was treated as unquestionable business advice—right up there with having a polished logo and a business card. But it's 2026 now. Social media platforms have become storefronts. AI assistants answer customer questions instantly. Marketplaces, apps, and directories promise to "replace" traditional websites altogether.
        </p>

        <p class="text-brand-sky/80 mb-8 leading-relaxed">
          So the question is this: <strong>Does your business really need a website anymore?</strong>
        </p>

        <p class="text-brand-sky/80 mb-8 leading-relaxed italic">
          The short answer: Most businesses still do—but not for the reasons you might think. The long answer is where things get very interesting.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mt-16 mb-8 flex items-center gap-4">
          <span class="text-brand-accent">01.</span> The Big Myth: "Social Media Replaced Websites"
        </h2>
        <p class="text-brand-sky/80 mb-8">
            Many businesses today operate entirely on platforms like Instagram, TikTok, WhatsApp, LinkedIn, Etsy, or Google Business Profiles. And to be totally clear—that can sometimes work, especially in the early stages.
        </p>

        <div class="bg-brand-dark/50 border border-white/5 p-8 rounded-2xl mb-12">
            <h4 class="text-white font-bold mb-4">But here's the uncomfortable truth:</h4>
            <p class="text-brand-sky/80 m-0">
                You don't <strong>OWN</strong> those platforms. You're renting attention. Algorithms change. Reach drops. Accounts get restricted, hacked, or shut down—sometimes without explanation. A business built entirely on a platform it doesn't control is always one policy update away from invisibility.
            </p>
            <p class="text-brand-cyan font-bold mt-4 m-0">A website is different. It's the only digital space that is fully yours.</p>
        </div>

        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mt-16 mb-8 flex items-center gap-4">
          <span class="text-brand-accent">02.</span> Why You Still Need a Website in 2026
        </h2>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mt-8 mb-4">Your Business's Source of Truth</h3>
        <p class="text-brand-sky/80 mb-8">
            When people hear about your business, the first thing they still do is Google you. Your website answers: Are you legit? What exactly does your business offer? Who are you for? How can I contact or do business with you? <strong>No website = unanswered questions.</strong>
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mt-8 mb-4">Builds Trust Faster Than Any Platform</h3>
        <p class="text-brand-sky/80 mb-8">
            A clean, clear website signals professionalism in a way social profiles can't always match. A business with a proper domain feels established. Pricing, policies, and contact details feel safer. Trust is currency—and your website is your online vault.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mt-8 mb-4">It Works While You Sleep</h3>
        <p class="text-brand-sky/80 mb-8">
            Your website doesn't need daily posting, trending sounds, or constant engagement. It can capture leads, book appointments, answer FAQs, sell products, and educate customers 24/7 without chasing social algorithms.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mt-8 mb-4">It Future-Proofs Your Business</h3>
        <p class="text-brand-sky/80 mb-12">
            Many AI search tools and assistants now pull information directly from business websites, not just social media posts. No website = fewer chances to be discovered in the AI-driven web.
        </p>

        <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-brand-blue/10 to-transparent border border-brand-blue/20 p-8 my-16 rounded-3xl">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-6">The New Rule for 2026</h3>
          <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
            <div>
              <p class="text-brand-accent font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-sm mb-4">You Don't Need:</p>
              <ul class="space-y-2 list-none p-0">
                <li class="text-brand-sky/60 flex items-center gap-2">✗ A massive website</li>
                <li class="text-brand-sky/60 flex items-center gap-2">✗ A complicated build</li>
                <li class="text-brand-sky/60 flex items-center gap-2">✗ Dozens of pages</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="text-brand-cyan font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-sm mb-4">But You Do Need:</p>
              <ul class="space-y-2 list-none p-0">
                <li class="text-white flex items-center gap-2">✓ A clear message</li>
                <li class="text-white flex items-center gap-2">✓ One place that explains what you do</li>
                <li class="text-white flex items-center gap-2">✓ One place you fully control</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mt-16 mb-8 text-center">The Bottom Line</h2>
        <p class="text-brand-sky/80 mb-12 text-center text-xl italic max-w-2xl mx-auto">
            "The smartest businesses don't ask, 'Do we need a website?' They ask, 'What role should our website play?'"
        </p>

        <!-- CTA Section -->
        <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-brand-blue to-brand-darkest p-12 rounded-[2rem] text-center relative overflow-hidden">
          <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-[radial-gradient(circle_at_50%_50%,rgba(0,255,255,0.1),transparent_70%)]"></div>
          <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-5xl font-black text-white mb-6 relative z-10 text-center">Need a Website That Works?</h2>
          <p class="text-xl text-white/80 mb-10 relative z-10 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
            Contact us for a high-end, premium website that actually brings you customers.
          </p>
          <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 justify-center relative z-10">
            <a href="/contact" class="bg-white text-brand-darkest px-10 py-4 rounded-xl font-bold text-lg hover:bg-brand-sky transition-all">
              Get Your Website
            </a>
            <a href="/services/web-design" class="bg-black/20 backdrop-blur-md text-white border border-white/20 px-10 py-4 rounded-xl font-bold text-lg hover:bg-black/30 transition-all">
              View Design Services
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="mt-24 p-8 bg-brand-dark/50 border border-white/5 rounded-2xl text-center">
            <p class="text-brand-sky/60 text-sm mb-4">
                This article was written and published by <strong>Shelby Web Company</strong> to help local businesses thrive in the digital age.
            </p>
            <p class="text-brand-sky/60 text-sm m-0">
                Ready to level up your online presence? Visit <a href="/" class="text-brand-cyan hover:underline">www.shelbywebco.com</a>.
            </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Footer navigation -->
      <footer class="mt-24 pt-12 border-t border-white/5 flex flex-wrap gap-8 items-center justify-between">
        <a href="/blog" class="text-brand-sky/60 hover:text-white transition-colors flex items-center gap-2">
          <svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M15 19l-7-7 7-7"/></svg>
          Back to Blog
        </a>
        <div class="flex gap-6">
          <a href="/" class="text-brand-sky/60 hover:text-white transition-colors">Home</a>
          <a href="/about" class="text-brand-sky/60 hover:text-white transition-colors">About Us</a>
          <a href="/contact" class="text-brand-sky/60 hover:text-white transition-colors">Contact</a>
        </div>
      </footer>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
